    "L6_top_supported_1": "For example, given a spatial region , Casini defines the entropy on the left-hand side of the Bekenstein bound as \nS_V = S(\\rho_V) - S(\\rho^0_V) = - \\mathrm{tr}(\\rho_V \\log \\rho_V) + \\mathrm{tr}(\\rho_V^0 \\log \\rho_V^0)\nwhere S(\\rho_V) is the Von Neumann entropy of the reduced density matrix \\rho_V associated with V in the excited state , and S(\\rho^0_V) is the corresponding Von Neumann entropy for the vacuum state .",
    "L6_top_supported_2": "Suppose we have a black hole of mass , then the Schwarzschild radius of the black hole is {{tmath|1= R_\\text{bh} \\sim {GM}/{c^2} }}, and the Bekenstein–Hawking entropy of the black hole is {{tmath|1= \\sim \\frac{kc^3 R_\\text{bh}^2}{\\hbar G} \\sim {kGM^2}/{\\hbar c} }}.",
    "L6_top_risky_1": "Now take a box of energy , entropy , and side length .",
    "L6_top_risky_2": "a *negative* localized energy.",
